@node "Introduction" "Introduction"

                        @{b}Introduction@{ub}

    Thanks to Datatypes, an app can load files (eg. pictures), without
knowing the type of the file. It can load GIF, JPEG or PNG pictures
without specific code.

    But few (old) commercial apps use this feature which comes with Workbench 3.0.

    It's the purpose goal of HappyDT: HappyDT acts just like a filter between
programms and loaded files . When an app tries to load a file of an unknown type,
HappyDT converts it in a temporary IFF file using datatypes. In this way, the app acts
just as if it loaded an IFF file. More, HappyDT can intercept the saving process of an app.
and so change the format of the saved file.
    In addition, if the file is packed, HappyDT can unpack it with Xpk or Xfd.
    Currently, HappyDT support Picture, Sound and Anim datatypes kinds.
@endnode

